column1: calculation based on the amount of time, measured in units of USER_HZ (1/100ths of a second on most architectures, use sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK) to obtain the right value),  that  the  system spent in user mode, user mode with low priority (nice), system mode, and the idle task, respectively.  The last value should be USER_HZ times the second entry in the uptime pseudo-file.
